    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Status of Rumex palustris (Polygonaceae) in the flora of Iran: an overview of current taxonomy, anatomy and ecology" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731916>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731918>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731920>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731922>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731924> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731916>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. The sample of Rumex palustris stored at HUMZ (No. 9115)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7731916/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731918>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Rumex palustris. A. Habitat; B & C. Habitus in the field; D & E. Inflorescence; F. Stem surface, glabrous or sparsely minute papillate; G. Fruits with articulated pedicels; H. Valves, dentate and tuberculate, three per fruit (down), rarely five (up); I. Achenes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7731918/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731920>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Global distribution map of Rumex palustris (up, showing colorful parts, with some modification from POWO 2023 and Euro+Med, 2023), focusing mainly on its position in north Iran (down, showing red triangle)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7731920/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731922>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Anatomical micrographs of stem in Rumex palustris. A, B, C and D showing cross-sections at 40×, 100×, 400× and 400× magnifications, respectively, and E showing longitudinal section of epidermis with 400× magnifications.Abbreviations: Cu = cuticle, Ep = epidermis, Co = collenchyma, Cp = parenchymatous cortex, Lc = laticifer cells, En = endodermis, Lv = large vascular bundle, Sv = small vascular bundle, Sc = sclerenchymatous ring, Xy = xylem, Ph = phloem, Cr = Crystal, Pp = parenchymatous pith, Ps = papillose." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7731922/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7731924>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Anatomical micrographs of leaf epidermis in Rumex species. R. palustris: A. longitudinal section of lower epidermis, B. longitudinal section of upper epidermis, and C. cross section of leaf. R. dentatus: D.epidermal cells, and F.stellate trichome.R. maritimus: E. epidermal cells, and G. peltate trichome.A–C illustrations were observed under 400× magnification, and others (D–G) were reprinted (with copy right permission from Paul & Chowdhury 2021, ekbif@naver.com). Abbreviations: St = stomata, Pt = peltate trichome (or peltate gland), Lc = laticifer cells, Cr-d = druse crystals, Cr-s = sand crystals, T-pt = two-celled peltate trichomes (or two-celled peltate glands), O-pt = one-celled peltate trichomes, Cc = crystalliferous cells. Arrow shows the straight cell walls of epidermis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7731924/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

